cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and investigates the properties of bag-of-n-grams sentence representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information encoding and prediction tasks, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
